= El destape

MÉXICO, D.F., noviembre de 1969 —

It is Echeverría.

The announcement comes, as tradition requires, from someone else's mouth — the CTM "spontaneously" proclaims him, the party organs discover they had always admired him, and by nightfall the *cargada* is at full gallop: governors, senators, and union chiefs stampeding to declare a loyalty they invented that morning. The losers perform the rite's final beauty: Ortiz Mena and Martínez Manautou, who at breakfast were the future of the Republic, appear at the candidate's side by dinner, smiling the smile of men swallowing an anvil.

In the Party's basement office the significance needs no seminar: the Secretary of Gobernación of the second of October — the man whose signature ran the DFS, the Federal Security that filled Lecumberri, the apparatus of that night in the plaza — will be President of the Republic for six years. And already the strangeness begins: his people whisper of an *apertura*, of dialogue with the youth, of turning pages. The same hand that signed is now extended.

- @continuidad: Read it plainly: the system has promoted the policeman. Prepare accordingly.
- @grieta: Read the whisper too: guilty men buy indulgences. An opening bought with blood is still an opening — position for it.

